ğŸ“˜ Definition:
Constructor ek special method hota hai jo object create karte waqt automatically call hota hai.

ğŸ”‘ Constructor ke features:
| Property              | Description                        |
| --------------------- | ---------------------------------- |
| Name                  | Same as class name                 |
| Return type           | âŒ No return type (not even `void`) |
| Call hota kab hai?    | Jab object banta hai               |
| Overloading possible? | âœ”ï¸ Yes                             |



âœ… Syntax:

class Car {
    Car() {  // Constructor
        System.out.println("Car constructor called");
    }
}



âœ… Example with Constructor:

class Student {
    String name;

    // Constructor
    Student() {
        name = "Unknown";
        System.out.println("Constructor called");
    }

    void display() {
        System.out.println("Name: " + name);
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Student s1 = new Student(); // ğŸ‘ˆ Constructor auto-called
        s1.display();
    }
}


EXAMPLE 2

class A {
    A() {
        System.out.println("Bike is ready");
    }

    void bike() {
        System.out.println("Riding bike");
    }
}

class main {
    public static void main(String[] arg) {
        A a1 = new A();    // âœ… Constructor auto-called
        a1.bike();         // âœ… Method call
    }
}
